column2: an object
column3: and an action. A prohibition is a triple similar to a permission
column4: but with a negative action. The overall structure of an access control policy can be represented as a directed graph. The nodes of the graph are the subjects
column6: and actions of the policy. The edges of the graph represent the relationships between the nodes. Each edge is labeled with the type of relationship it represents. For example
column7: an edge from a subject node to an object node would represent the fact that the subject is allowed to access the object.
